        "text_snippet": "The hydroisomerization process for the crude soybean oil was conducted in a high-pressure flow reactor system with a stationary bed of 50 cm³... Hydroisomerization studies investigated the influence of temperature ranging from 260 to 340 °C, pressure from 2 to 5 MPa, and LHSV (0.25 to 1) at a GHSV of 100.",
